# Insight AnalytiX Installation Guide

Use this guide to install the Insight AnalytiX node and connect it to the StorageX management console. This procedure ensures your node is correctly configured for data discovery and analytics.

## Prerequisites
Before you begin the installation, verify that the target server meets these requirements:

* **Operating system:** RHEL 8.x or Ubuntu 20.04 LTS.
* **Hardware:** 8 vCPU, 16 GB RAM, and 100 GB available disk space.
* **Network:** Ports **443** (HTTPS) and **8080** must be open for communication between the node and the StorageX server.
* **Permissions:** Root or `sudo` privileges are required to execute installation scripts.

---

## Install the AnalytiX engine
Use the command-line interface (CLI) to deploy the engine.

### 1. Download and extract the package
Navigate to your staging directory and retrieve the latest build:

```bash
wget [https://downloads.datadynamics.com/insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz](https://downloads.datadynamics.com/insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz)
tar -xvf insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz
cd insight-analytix-v2.1
```
### 2. Run the installation script
```bash
Use the `--management-ip` flag to link the node to your StorageX console:
sudo ./install.sh --management-ip <IP_ADDRESS> --node-name "<NODE_NAME>"
```
### 3. Verify the service status
Confirm that the services are active and running:
```bash
systemctl status analytix-engine
```
## Troubleshooting
Refer to the table below to resolve common installation issues.
| Issue | Cause | Solution |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Connection timeout** | Port 443 is blocked by a firewall. | Run `ufw allow 443` or check network security groups. |
| **Invalid management IP** | The IP address is unreachable. | Ping the server to verify connectivity and re-run the script. |
| **Insufficient disk space** | The `/opt` partition has less than 10 GB available. | Clean up logs or expand the partition before restarting setup. |
## Post-Installation
After a successful installation, log in to the StorageX Insight Analytics dashboard to verify the node appears in the managed resources list and to initiate your first scan.